HEADWORD: Procuracy
<hw>Proc"u*ra*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Procuracies</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[LL.
<ets>procuratia</ets>: cf. F. <ets>procuratie</ets>. See
<er>Procuration</er>, and cf,. <er>Proxy</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The office or act of a proctor or procurator;
management for another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Authority to act for another; a proxy.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Procuration</ent>⟦br⟧
